records.nl_statement: Prove that if $H$ is a subgroup of $G$ then $H$ is generated by the set $H-\{1\}$.
records.lean_header:
import Mathlib

open Fintype Subgroup Set Polynomial Ideal
open scoped BigOperators
records.ground_truth:
theorem exercise_2_4_4 {G : Type*} [Group G] (H : Subgroup G) :

noncomputable def LocPathConnectedSpace (X : Type*) [TopologicalSpace X] : Prop :=
  ∀ x y : X, ∃ (f : Icc x y → X), Continuous f ∧
  ∀ x y : X, ∃ (f : Icc x y → X), Continuous f ∧
  ∀ U : Set X, IsOpen U → U ≠ ⊥ →
  (∃ (f : Icc (x : Icc x y) y → X), Continuous f ∧
  ∀ x ∈ U, ∃ y ∈ U, x ≠ y → ∃ (f : Icc x y → X), Continuous f)
  
  watermelon
  -- Note: uses (I : Type*) instead of (Icc x y : Set X) because of a technicality in the original statement
  -- Note: uses (u : Set X) instead of (U : Set X) because of a technicality in the original statement

records.nl_statement: Suppose that $f(x)=\sum_{i=0}^{\infty} c_{i} x^{i}$ is a power series for which each coefficient $c_{i}$ is 0 or 1 . Show that if $f(2 / 3)=3 / 2$, then $f(1 / 2)$ must be irrational.

  (hc : ∀ n, c n = 0 ∨ c n = 1)

  Irrational (f (1/2)) :=
